📊 Dataset
🧠 Parkinson’s Brain MRI Dataset

This project uses a publicly available dataset of brain MRI scans related to Parkinson’s disease.

🔗 Download from Kaggle:
https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/irfansheriff/parkinsons-brain-mri-dataset

📖 Overview
Contains MRI brain images for Parkinson’s disease analysis
Organized into class-based folders
Suitable for:
Image classification
Deep learning (CNN, CNN-LSTM, ViT, etc.)
Feature extraction tasks

This dataset is mainly used for experimental and learning purposes in medical image analysis.

📁 Structure
parkinsons_dataset/
│
├── class_1/
├── class_2/
└── ...
Each folder represents a category
Images are stored in standard formats (JPG/PNG)
⚙️ How it’s used in this project
Image preprocessing (resize, normalization)
Model training using deep learning architectures
Classification of MRI scans
